# Smoke Test Enforcement

## Purpose
- Enforce a repeatable loop: change -> build -> smoke -> fix -> re-verify.
- Applies to code changes; documentation-only edits are exempt unless requested.

## Mandatory Triggers
- If `packages/*/src/**` is changed:
  - Build the affected package(s) with `pnpm --filter ... build`.
- If `apps/api-server/src/**` is changed:
  - Build `@robota-sdk/api-server`.
  - Run API smoke checks for affected endpoints.
- If `apps/web/src/**` is changed:
  - Build `@robota-sdk/web`.
  - Verify key route health (at minimum `/dag-designer` if DAG UI is touched).

## Execution Rules
- Before starting dev servers, check existing terminal logs and avoid duplicate processes.
- If port conflicts occur, stop stale processes and restart the intended server.
- Do not treat build success as final verification; smoke checks are required.

## Failure Policy
- On any build/smoke failure:
  - Stop and identify root cause from logs/output.
  - Apply a proper fix (no workaround shortcuts).
  - Re-run the same verification path until success.

## Completion Criteria
- Mark implementation complete only when:
  - Required build commands pass.
  - Required smoke checks pass.
  - Reported behavior matches expected outcomes.
